{
  "texts": [
    "The orange ones represent the message types that appear in the appropriate states but do not trigger any state transition (so there is no state change).",
    "The blue ones represent the types that appear in the inappropriate state that would be directly rejected by the server.",
    "From Figure 5, we can see that there are 81%, 74%, 89%, and 69% client requests, respectively, that can induce state transitions to different states.",
    "Additionally, approximately 17%, 16%, 10%, and 30% client requests can still be accepted and processed by the server although they do not trigger the state change.",
    "These messages are still potentially useful to cover more code branches although they failed to cover more states."
  ]
}